		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I really think Lunrak has a very good point. I want to raid myself, but in order to do that, I have to leave my guild and join another, that can come up with the big number's required. My guild can get two groups at any time, three groups with notice, or planned up to 4 groups, and even then it might not be 4 full groups. However, they are all willing. With raid number lower'd, my guild would progress. The only problem I see with it, is everyone wants to do all the content, meaning content already in game that does require, out of just the amount of mobs that need to be took out. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The funny thing I have noticed is that no real&nbsp; raider is challenging any of it, outside of Naubu. Even Shar has only come in to acknowledge certain things that happen (Flaunting, etc.), but hasn't really tried to put down this idea. If raider's don't seem to see any real threat to it, or anything that really would hinder (at this point, I am believing it would enhance the game for everyone, casual and raider alike) the game or themselves, then.... I just would like to know exactly Why not?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Fabled, it's hard to comment on things you say, since everything is bassically easily turned back around. If I say it would be better if gear was more equal, you will say "Why do I need it in content I am in?" then myself or someone else will say "Why do they need it in content I am in?" It's not about what's necessary, it's about balance and fairness. Gear isn't the same as AA, nor is it the same as Level... If I am level 65 with the best gear I can possibly have through whatever means (raiding, etc.) and your gear at level 70 is only half as good as mine, I don't care how much AA's you have, or that your 5 levels higher, I am gonna out tank you. Give me gear that is scaled down, but still slightly better, and if you have 400 more AA's, your surely gonna out tank me. However if we are equal in AA and in Level, their is only one deciding factor that will determine who is going to survive better, and that is gear. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In fact, if I have the best gear, and you have what you have right now, I will out tank you anywhere, and not have to have one AA to do it. I will aggree to dissagree with you way of thinking, I just don't know where else I can take you for it to sink in. My guess is your not wanting it too. No post of yours has suggested to me that you understand what is being said, even when you try to examine it. Don't get me wrong, I like your posts, and I like reading them, even if we don't see eye to eye.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							"One falsehood destroys a thousand truths." "Do not think of yourself higher than you ought to think" "If you are not guilty of the robbery then you should not hold on to the loot!" -NOEL BRYSON, Ph

The wise discuss ideas, the normal discuss events, the ignorant discuss other's.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
