		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>That's pretty much what I did, I simply joined a guild that raided. It's a big change of pace no doubt, but the family feel is still there. I think there are at least 10 guilds or more on my server who can field 50 plus person raids.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I understand the in between idea, however, it was said that 54 seems the right number......I think you could get by with 36. Tactics change based on numbers in some situations. Believe me, in some of the raid zones you need 50. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>High end though is for high end, Anguished geared folks are geared for anquished style raids. There really is no way to properly build a zone that could acomadate xp groups of high end raiders, none of the gear those single group named drop would be as good as what high end 54 person raid mobs droped.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I guess that's whats difficult to explain. I am Qivic/Time geared and have alot of augs from everywhere. I'm built to off tank/tank mobs in gOD raid zones. Single group content, even in expansions that are newer like Rss, are easier for me to do than for a casuals.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;From my perspective I think all single group mobs and zones are actually designed for casuals, maybe high end casuals for some of them, but casuals none the less. Raiders have gear designed for raiding, so have a much easier time in zones designed for casuals. The gap exists because the two groups are on seperate paths.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
