<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12248#M12248">104</a> of 332
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 275 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Pickup raids are fine for named mobs (Vindi cycle, Rhag's cycle, etc.), Lower tier flagging, even POI, BOT, POV Dragon, etc.. yes. They are ok for doing Epic's (any really). But trying to get a whole raid to understand how to take out the Emperor of SSRA, and getting the mezz targets for individual's, etc. is not likely gonna have a success. There is numerous mobs on the path to progression that just takes to long to try and explain to a full raid what every individual needs to do, when they don't know (Which is why the desire for a guild that does indeed "know" what to do) what to do. I've done PU for POI Dragon and Behemoth, successfully, Bot key farming in POV, POV dragon, even a couple in SRT, but when doing tier two and higher, the problem is having enough able to get in the zone and do it (Tactic's, etc.). Battleblade, I know your hardcore to the bone, so I (believe it or not) value your thoughts. I am not going to say it's impossible, but you have to know it's a bit unreasonable to actually do Time without at least a Time flagged guild hosting it. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For the record, that's exactly how my guild has decided to do things. There is two channels we are involved with that has at times over 100 people in them. They have been around before global chat's were made in the game (/general, etc.). I have done Tier one PU raids, tier two PU raids, but getting to the next level has been a bit troublesome.. I get the people, just can't get them all in:-(</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I did a few higher tier's with actual Raid guild's that hosted them, but without them to 85 in some of the key class's (Cleric's, DPS, etc.) it wouldn't have been possible. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>VT I believe we are gonna be able to get the guild key'd for actually, and in the process we will probably get more and more Raidlike, and less and less casual, to proceed. My personal thoughts on what your talking about is just well, backwards. Your looking at having someone say "Hey everyone, I need my (Zone) flag, Come to POT to help me get it!!" is not going to work. However "(Guild name) is hosting a Tactics raid for POP Flagging, meet in POT, Raid starts in 30 minutes!" Just might work. IF only two or three know what to do, well, I think you know what that leads to.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I generally can get people together pretty easily. In fact, I wanted help on something a few months back, and all I did was tell someone I needed a hand. That person tells a couple chat channels I need help, and here come's&nbsp;a quarter of&nbsp;my friends list (Ton's of Raider's on my friends list, FYI) to help me with a mob I only needed a snarer and a healer for... But yet, I got 3 full groups in like 15 minutes without doing anything but asking 1 person "Know any healer's that can help me kill this mob?". All they knew was I asked for help (A rare occassion), and here they come. PU Raids aren't the answer to true progression though. I do know some singular individuals that have been able to get into enough flag raids to get up to time flagged, but they did it by themselves, not as a unit. In my guild alone, there is a dozen flagged for EP, and half a dozen flagged for time and higher. The guild as a whole might be able to consider tier one as a backflag. A few people in the guild has their VT keys. These are people that left raid guild's, because they couldn't play as much as the rest of their guild, but still wanted to play. All of them are still thought of as friends to that guild, and there friends in those guilds will come help when able.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The thing is, most guild's want self reliance, and PU isn't being self reliant. A raid path of up to 24 people, would enable them to be Self Reliant though. And it would provide them a way of showing YOU they are not lazy. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
