		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>In thier defence, after going through several of the gOD raid zones. I can understand some of the attitude sometimes, those zones are a real PIA to get through. Frustration seems to be the objective for half of it. Some of the events are just silly, and can be a real headache to get finished. For instance, traps that constantly reset themselves, traps that move around, mobs that can see through the rogues special hide ability, even though they are the primary trap disarmers. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Some of the zones seemed designed by people who only wanted to kill you as many times as they could for a giggle. After doing Uqua and Inkutu for several weeks I certainly expected some decent looking gear to drop, and no, stuff like WoS items wouldn't cut the mustard. The reward has to be so uber for raid encounters like that or no one would go back.&nbsp; If AoW, back when he was the top mob, droped only bronze armor, you think he would be on rotations?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It isn't just risk/reward. The reward has to be worth the risk that raid zone really represents in time and deaths, and in some cases just worth the headache the idiot event was. Don't get me wrong many raid encounters are fun, but some........&nbsp; I suspect a saddest designed them. If an ecounter has a constant 5k aoe going off every 10 seconds and it has a -1000 on your save and the mob hits for 5k and yadda yadda, it better drop something with mega stats,ac, hps, and abilities. If it didn't, then foreget me wasteing my time on it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Think how disapointing Time would be if it only droped gear that You could get off Vox.</DIV>	
