<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12255#M12255">110</a> of 332
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 247 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
The-Fabled-IksarSK-Drinal wrote:
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Two things to note from your rant:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A) Raiding is a **SMURF**... it takes hard work, effort, and an organized group of well played characters.</DIV>
<DIV>B) Either you join a guild that raids, make one yourself, or quit because it's all too much work.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So basically, there's a lot of hard work going on to take out the most challenging content that gives the best rewards, and since you don't want in... don't want to do it yourself... and can't live without it... there's a problem.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now, I know your parents might have told you otherwise... but not everybody can be an astronaut...&nbsp;especially the kids that say they deserve it without thinking they should put the effort into it...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>(now President, that's feasible... hehe, sorry, cheap shot, but I couldn't resist)</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>First it wasn't a rant.&nbsp; It is my opinion and point of view, agree disagree whatever.&nbsp; Second those choices are what I see as the option for someone who absolutely wants to raid, but simply can't.&nbsp; Do you see another choice?&nbsp; </P>
<P>A) Yes I am aware of that and feel it should require hardwork and effort...but not 54 people.</P>
<P>B)Addressed joining a raid guild already, for some it just isn't possible.&nbsp; Making a guild, I pretty much explained that in the post you quoted.&nbsp; I've seen people leave, not because it is too much work, but because no matter how much work they put into it, it counted for nothing.&nbsp; It helped them achieve little if any of their goals.&nbsp; If their goal is to raid, and because of the dynamics of raiding they can only suceed by giving up their lives then that is too much to ask.&nbsp; And I am not saying&nbsp;raiders have no lives, I'm saying some people, to become raiders would have to give up all semblance of a life in order to do it, and that is an unjust price to pay to satisfy the hardcore who scream for more effort by those players.</P>
<P>The point I am trying to make is we keep wanting to make everything black and white as far as effort goes.&nbsp; It always seems to be raid the way we do or go home and shut up.&nbsp; That isn't very condusive to community harmony or balance.&nbsp; You do have to put effort forth, I totally agree, but why does that effort have to come in the form of finding 53 friends when challenging, fun, rewarding raids can be designed around smaller forces?&nbsp; There is no longer a logical reason to force guilds to the sizes they are for raiding when every encounter can now be instanced, and tuned for a max number of players and a set of gear.&nbsp; The only reason it continues is because it has always been that way.&nbsp; That is typically a horrid reason to keep doing something.&nbsp; </P>
<P>What would it hurt if raiding was changed in&nbsp;a way that made it more likely and more plausible for more of the community to get involved in it?&nbsp; I don't think it would hurt much, it would actually help in the long run.&nbsp; That is all I'm trying to say.&nbsp; If you'll go back a few pages and posts you'll note I am not talking about narrowing the gap in gear between raiders and non-raiders.&nbsp; I am talking about increasing the number of people that are able to raid by spreading it out over many guilds rather than 5-10.&nbsp; That just makes alot more sense.&nbsp; No not everyone can be an astronaut, but like many other real-world analogies that has no place here, this is a GAME it is not life and comparing it to the real-word seems as absurd as ever.&nbsp; If all I wanted was something exactly like real life, I would not be playing a game.&nbsp; </P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<img src=" http://mywebpages.comcast.net/lunrak/LunrakSOESig.gif"><br><A href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1125375">Lunrak of Fennin Ro</A><br><br>If you have to tell me how uber you are...then you aren't. <br>If you are uber I will already know, and wont need you to remind me.
							</div>
								
