			>
			<DIV>"but not everybody can be an astronaut...&nbsp;especially the kids that say they deserve it without thinking they should put the effort into it...
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>(now President, that's feasible... hehe, sorry, cheap shot, but I couldn't resist)"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ha ha ha. It's funny that I aggree on one thing in your post, and it's in ().</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I haven't seen anyone say they wanted something for nothing though. Maybe your not reading the same posts I am though, who knows. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you think that having an alternate route with less people, and of course a lesser reward (which was said already), is getting something for nothing, then I guess your reading the same thing, but not letting it sinc in. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The whole time Lunrak has been posting, I've been visualizing a 24 raid in current content being able to progress and getting rewards compatible to maybe an expansion or two behind at the end of it... Maybe OOW would lead to being able to get into Time or at least the EP zones (as was actually fear'd right before it actually come out). DoN giving some kind of access to GOD content, or DoD giving access to some farmable OOW content, and so on, with alternate routes of progression requireing less people, but going up against harder (yet lower number'd) mobs. As much as I try, I can't see a logical reason to deny this request, trying to be as optimistic as I can, I can only feel that:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. This would help those people that want to raid, but can't get into the actual Raid guilds, lacking flags and keys required.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Would help family guilds that want to raid, but don't have the number's required to advance. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Would help Raid guild's backflag for newer players in all but the last expansion or so.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Maybe someone wouldn't like it, but I&nbsp;really don't see anything that would hinder anyone, or even trivialise anything.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>
