<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Explain to me how you're spending the same amount of time as a raider, yet the raider is staying up to the wee hours of the morning... wouldn't that mean the raider is spending MORE time (unless time magically stops for them after you've gone to bed...)?&nbsp; And if they're spending the SAME amount of time as you, then wouldn't it be correct that they spent MORE time prior to this very moment doing all those difficult recruiting processes that you think is so hard to accomplish?&nbsp; and that now they're spending that same amount of time as you, only doing MUCH more challenging content?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>An unsuccessful open raid channel is about as popular as an unsuccessful guild... nobody is preventing you from running a highly efficient successful raid... and nobody is preventing you from having a very poorly run guild... it's up to you to make the best out of your resources... and if you're as good as you 'think' you are... you wouldn't have a problem joining one of those raiding guilds in the first place... especially since the rest of your server is such a bunch of childish hacks as you put it.</DIV>
