<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;JazzyJoyce wrote:<BR></P>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The whole time Lunrak has been posting, I've been visualizing a 24 raid in current content being able to progress and getting rewards compatible to maybe an expansion or two behind at the end of it...</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think what you are asking for is not unreasonable in the scheme of things within the game but I do not see it as a feasable optoion for everquest.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Currently we have solo play, group play and raid play and the raid play has been reduced from 72 players to 54 (a step in the right direction), the problem as I see it is that youa re asking for a new tier of gameplay aimed at the 24 raid size that you envisage - that will take up developers and designers time, now if this was a brand new game then perhaps they could build it in but with this established old brute of a game with all the issues of bugs, fixes that haven't been fixed, new expansions and the ole class balancing act - I cant see how or where the time and effort required to bring in 24 raiding is going to be achieved. This leaves you with what Lunark said PU raiding (sucks), creating a new guild (possible but a lot more of your valuable time is now going to be devoted to leading and running a raid, joining an established guild or just be content to do the group and solo thing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If your desire is greater than those within your guild you have 2 options ask for a regular raid schedule and if ask for specific targets and aims for the guild and take responsibility within your existing guild to bring this about - if that means recruiting new members then you have to do it or alternatively say you love your guild members loads but be honest with them and leave for a guild that will provide enough to fulfil your desires.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now I know going to a raiding guild is a lot to take on board and some due to work patterns cant do this but SOE has said over and over again that the bigger the force needed to overcome a monster will provide bigger and better rewards - with this mental attidude from SOE and the unlikely introduction of new 24 man raid play being introduced then you have to decide for yourselves which is more important for you&nbsp;from the current options available to you and decide whether the 24 man raid thing is likely to be brought in and make a decision - it's not a comfortable decision.</DIV>
<DIV><BR>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
