			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
The-Fabled-IksarSK-Drinal wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I'm so tired of hearing being in the top end raid force of 54 people as the <STRONG><EM>only </EM></STRONG>way to progress.</DIV>
<DIV>No, it's the only way to get the best gear.... there are MORE lower count raids and MORE high end group encounters than there have ever been in EQ and NOBODY is complaining about them...&nbsp;come back when you're fully Dreadspire geared.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff66>Then please tell us how a force of 24 can progress through PoP content, GoD content, OoW content. It isn't only about gear it is also about progressing through content outside of just the normal group content.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The only people complaining are those that see the loot from the 54+ person raids and think that the gap is too big.&nbsp; And finally, I'm tired of hearing people complain about that gap while arguing the difficulty of raiding.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff66>Yet how many times now have I said the gap isn't too big?&nbsp; Are you reading the entire post or just flying off a few key comments?&nbsp; I'm not arguing the difficulty of raiding.&nbsp; What I'm arguing is the need for smaller raid force content, that 54 is too large, it ads a level of difficulty outside of the skill of the player.&nbsp; You can be an extremely skillful player, but if you can't pull together 53 other people you will never see that content or gear period and why should you have to pull together that many people.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Explain to me how you're spending the same amount of time as a raider, yet the raider is staying up to the wee hours of the morning... wouldn't that mean the raider is spending MORE time (unless time magically stops for them after you've gone to bed...)?&nbsp; And if they're spending the SAME amount of time as you, then wouldn't it be correct that they spent MORE time prior to this very moment doing all those difficult recruiting processes that you think is so hard to accomplish?&nbsp; and that now they're spending that same amount of time as you, only doing MUCH more challenging content?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff66>How about the raider is logging in at about the time I am logging of.&nbsp; Spending 5 hours raiding.&nbsp; I spent my 5 hours in game before they even got there, then I spend a major chunk of Sat and Sun in game as well.&nbsp; There ya go, equal time in game.&nbsp; Now explain to me why real raiding, i.e. raid targets and raid gearing should only be for those that can muster a force of 54?&nbsp; Yes I am aware that small guilds can take 3 and 4 groups to go farm gear in what are essentially challenging group zones but that is not raiding, that is overpowering the content instead of taking on the challenge as it was intended.&nbsp; Raid content currently has the intent of being tuned for 54 person raids with a certain type of gear.&nbsp; I still have not seen a logical reason for it to remain at 54, care to give it a shot?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>An unsuccessful open raid channel is about as popular as an unsuccessful guild... nobody is preventing you from running a highly efficient successful raid... and nobody is preventing you from having a very poorly run guild... it's up to you to make the best out of your resources... and if you're as good as you 'think' you are... you wouldn't have a problem joining one of those raiding guilds in the first place... especially since the rest of your server is such a bunch of childish hacks as you put it.</DIV>
<P><FONT color=#ffff33>Actually the time involved, i.e. the time it takes to build a highly successful raid force is what prevents it from happening.&nbsp; I've watched a guild grow from the ground up to raiding time.&nbsp; It took them two years to break into time from ground zero and that is skipping VT.&nbsp; I don't know if you are aware of the difficulty of putting together a cohesive quality force of that size, but one major difficulty is that anymore it is very difficult to find players that want to wait 6 months let alone 24 to get to that point of raiding.&nbsp; When did I ever claim my skill at anything?&nbsp; I consider myself to be a competent player so please don't make assumptions about what I have and haven't claimed.&nbsp; As far as not having a problem joining an existing&nbsp;raiding guild I have already made that pretty clear why that isn't possible, but I'll spell it out for you yet again...there is ONE guild on my server that raids during a time when I can raid, the requirements for that guild (when recruiting is opened) include certain flags upto and including EP.&nbsp; As I have stated before the open raiding on my server appears to be dead.&nbsp; Haven't seen an OOC for an open flagging&nbsp;raid in PoK or PoT in a year.&nbsp; Haven't seen a call for an open raid for flagging in the "raid" channel in over a year.&nbsp; And again don't put words in my mouth, I did not say that the rest of the server is a bunch of childish hacks.&nbsp; I said a good chunk of the TWENTY FIVE people in the open raid channel are.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff66></FONT><BR>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
